an National University of the Arts.&nbsp;Hsu’s artistic practices utilize animation, video and installation to explore how memories are being perceived. He has a special interest in the reconstruction of past memories and events, whether is intimate moments or collective&nbsp;histories. Hsu’s videos illustrate our process of identifying our surroundings through interpretations of memories.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(334,1,'2020-04-29 13:17:59','2020-04-29 13:20:06',NULL,'Aojie Lin',NULL,'aojie-lin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Tag 1, Tag 2',NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Aojie Lin currently lives and works in Guangzhou. Most of his works&nbsp; draw inspirations from the mundane every experiences. Lin’s practices involve video, photography, drawing and text, feature acute sensibilities towards spontaneities and humors. Lin’s works are provocative in a sense that they covers concerns relating “the disjuncture between art and capitalism, annoyance with an artist’s social responsibilities, even frustration with his own ambition.” (ArtAisaPacific) His voice are expressed through mockery of those daily narrations.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(335,1,'2020-04-29 13:22:18','2020-04-29 13:54:28',NULL,'Ni Youyu',NULL,'ni-youyu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ni Youyu is a shanghai based multidisciplinary artist. “Viewing Ni Youyu’s work often leaves one with a spatial and temporal illusion.” Most of his art making process requires significant duration and and “go through a degree of uncertainty from gestation to completion.” His works are sometimes positioned apart from the realm of “contemporary art”, as the manner of artisans is deeply embed in his process.The nature of Ni’s works makes it hard for him to “produce works according to an exhibition theme in the manner of a modern artist.” (Perrotin New York)<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" href = \"https://www.niyouyu.com/\">website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(336,1,'2020-04-29 13:52:10','2020-04-29 13:52:10',NULL,'Lu Pingyuan',NULL,'lu-pingyuan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Lu Pingyuan lives and works in Shanghai. His works have specific interests in texts and fictional writings. Lu incorporates huge amount of nonlinear fictional stories into his practices, and text is considered one of his most frequently used medium. The unexpected, bizarre, and surrealistic writings of Lu provide viewers a glimpse into his contracted context. The writings challenge the boundaries between fantasies and physical realities, redefine the possible state of being of an artwork.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(337,1,'2020-04-29 13:54:47','2020-04-29 14:18:48',NULL,'Jiehao Su',NULL,'jiehao-su',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Jiehao Su is an artists working primarily with photography, video, text, and spatial installation. He was born in Guangdong, China and now based in Rhode Island. “He is particularly interested in the poetics and politics of everyday situations, the mediated reality in contemporary society, as well as the physical and metaphysical aspects of the world.”&nbsp;(<a href=\"http://jiehaosu.com\">jiehaosu.com</a>) Su’s practices employ an cinematic approach to explore “the notions of temporality and spatiality in the structure of narrative.”<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" href = \"https://jiehaosu.com/\">website</a><br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" href = \"(url)\">show</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(338,1,'2020-04-29 13:55:33','2020-04-29 13:55:33',NULL,'Ke peng',NULL,'ke-peng',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ke peng is a Los Angeles based photographer. She was born in Changsha and received her BFA in photography from Rhode Island School of Design. Ke’s works pay close attentions to the subtle connections between things, with an septic focus on the “distinctions within similarity”.<br>Her recent works explore the “colourful corners of China’s smaller cities”, (British Journal of Photography) feature a distinctive approach to observe those overly repetitive, familiar spaces.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" href = \"http://pengke.studio/\">pengke.studio</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(339,1,'2020-04-29 13:56:05','2020-04-29 13:56:05',NULL,'Mountain River Jump!',NULL,'mountain-river-jump',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Mountain River Jump! is an artist duo founded in 2016 by twin sisters Huang Shan and Huang He, who were born in 1985. The duo has a variety of creative formats in art, often applying \"divination consulting\" as a performance to examine the potential of such art medium, and to interact with the audience at the intrinsic level. With their studies into Oriental mysticism and folklore, the artists pry open the topics of identity politics, labor issues, feminism, life politics, modernity and others. They pay attention to the embodiment of mythological clues in a daily context, attempting to carry out \"psychoanalysis\" of the reality, and reflecting on the materialist culture within modern China and its psychological status. Huang Shan and Huang He presently works and lives in Foshan, Guangdong.” (yellowriver1985.com)<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(340,1,'2020-04-29 13:57:07','2020-04-29 13:57:07',NULL,'Tao Hui',NULL,'tao-hui',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Tao Hui lives and works in Beijing. He graduated from Sichuan Academy of Art with a painting degrees and now works as an installation based artist.&nbsp; Tao Hui’s video works draw inspirations from both personal memories and cultural characteristics (TV series, comedy shows and&nbsp; folklores),&nbsp; illustrates our processes of self-identification under constructed narrations. His prattles covers a variety of topic social identity. cultural crisis and&nbsp; gender identity. Tao’s self-established narratives are metaphorically relate to the cultural context of contemporary societies. The absurdities in his works are employed in a provocative manner.&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(341,1,'2020-04-29 13:57:58','2020-04-29 13:57:58',NULL,'Aaajiao',NULL,'aaajiao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Active online as a media artist, blogger, activist and programmer, aaajiao is the virtual persona of Shanghai- and Berlin- artist Xu Wenkai. Born in 1984—the title of George Orwell’s classic allegorical novel— and in one of China’s oldest cities, Xi’an, aaajiao’s art and works are marked by a strong dystopian awareness, literati spirits and sophistication. Many of aaajiao’s works speak to new thinkings, controversies and phenomenon around the Internet, with specific projects focusing on the processing of data, the blogsphere and China’s Great Fire Wall.” ( <a href=\"https://eventstructure.com/aaajiao\">https://eventstructure.com/aaajiao</a>)<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(342,1,'2020-04-29 13:58:20','2020-04-29 13:58:20',NULL,'Guan Xiao',NULL,'guan-xiao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Guan Xiao’s practices involve sculptures and video arts. She currently works in Beijing.&nbsp;<br>Her works actively explores cultural histories to identify their impacts on contemporary cultures, serving as a juxtaposition of the past and future. Guan’s sculptures pay close attentions to forms and materials that resembles life,&nbsp; including animal shells, scales and plant roots. “Her comparisons of regionally and chronologically disparate objects expose similarities among civilizations, regions, and eras while avoiding solid conclusions.”(<a href=\"http://artsy.net\">artsy.net</a>) Humors and resistances are well-integrated into her explorations.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(343,1,'2020-04-29 13:58:37','2020-04-29 13:58:37',NULL,'Yang Jian',NULL,'yang-jian',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Yang Jian is a curator and artist works based in Beijing. His practices encompass installation, video and performance. Yang casts doubts on the mundane everyday objects to speak against their functionalities. Contradictory and absurd statements&nbsp; are made out of his unexpected combinations of materials. The unplanned metaphors embodied in his sculptures speak aginst the established everyday logics. His works, embrace a calm and poetic manner, detach the chosen objects from their original cultural context.&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,1,'2020-04-29 13:58:54','2020-04-29 13:58:54',NULL,'Zhao Zhao',NULL,'zhao-zhao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Zhao Zhao was born in Xinjiang, China, in 1982. He graduated with a BFA from the Xinjiang Institute of Arts from the department of Oil Painting in 2003. Zhao Zhao’s multidisciplinary body of work is an inspection of China’s contemporary profile, and the socio-political consequences of individual human action. His abstract shattered glass paintings reveal a car accident he was involved in, and represents the ripple effect of action; his “Safe” sculptures substantiate his fellow citizens’ paranoid views on security.” (Chambers Fine Art) With confronting and bold commentaries on politics, His works challenges the traditions of social norms, indicates his unique opinions on Anarchism and anti-authoritarian.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(345,1,'2020-04-29 13:59:13','2020-04-29 13:59:13',NULL,'Guo Cheng',NULL,'guo-cheng',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Guo Cheng has a background of industrial and product design, currently lives and works in Shanghai. His art practices encompass installation, video and performance. Guo’s works examine the influences of booming technologies on our social and cultural awarenesses, as well as social interactions of individuals. Constructed machineries are important component of Guo’s installation. His works propose fictional imaginations of body extensions, in order to interpret how technologies cast influence on our day to day life.&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(346,1,'2020-04-29 13:59:35','2020-04-29 13:59:35',NULL,'Weiyi Li',NULL,'weiyi-li',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Weiyi Li is an artist weiyi.li, designer weiyiandfriends.com, curator bigbadgallery.com, publisher re-publication.com and retailor currently-available.com who lives and works between these five URLs.”(wiyi.li) Li has a text-based approach with her art practices. Her works re-interpret the collected texts and daily objects and reassign them to the viewers. The original functionalities of those chosen objects are altered by artist\'s objective understandings, which lead to intriguing associations.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(347,1,'2020-04-29 14:00:09','2020-04-29 14:00:09',NULL,'Luka Yuanyuan Yang',NULL,'luka-yuanyuan-yang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“ Luka Yuanyuan Yang graduated from London College of Communications, University of the Arts London with a BA (hons) in photography. She currently lives and works in Beijing, San Francisco or New York. Most of the time, Luka Yuanyuan Yang’s projects take the research and collected historical materials as the departure, and they evolve along with individual experiences relate to specific places. By creating narratives where facts and fiction coexist, she challenges the rigid and conventional interpretation of history and gives voices to subjects that have been forgotten, silenced, and misinterpreted. Yang creates visual narrative through photography, writings, video, artist books and performance.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" href = \"ocula.com\">website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(348,1,'2020-04-29 14:00:36','2020-04-29 14:00:36',NULL,'Shen Xin',NULL,'shen-xin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Shen Xin lives and works in London and Amsterdam. “ Through images and events, Shen explores emotions, value judgements and ethics that circulate through individual and collective subjects.” (k11artfoundation) Her recent project explores Buddhism under the context of western communities, with specific focus on the existing conflicts between Buddhism beliefs and&nbsp;patriarchal&nbsp;societies.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL);
